															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dankaar" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1790336); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1790336&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227303" alt="dankaar" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1790336)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dankaar" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1790336); return false;" >dankaar</a></span> <span class="odate time_1421988298 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Jan 2015 04:44</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2214397">
									

<p>#3/4 had the containment lights pop within 30 seconds. Lights do not work like that: I have six lights in my room replaced all at once, and they run for the same length of time. When one burnt out, none of the others did. Something other than the fact that they were installed at the same time had to occur (though it is still a reasonable precaution to not do that).</p>
<p>#5 is a situation where the SCP may or may not have affected the victim (the whole &quot;centered on fuel door&quot; is pretty telling), thereby negating any reasonable or forseeable actions that could have mitigated their death.</p>
<p>#6 is stuck in a stable and repeating time-loop, and had appeated both after and in a different spot than where the model said it would. Again, there is no reasonable or forseeable actions that could have changed the outcome.</p>
<p>So, I'm not seeing how these circumstances could have reasonably been protected against.</p>

							</div>

								
					
