				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/scorpion451" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1918720); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1918720&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227303" alt="Scorpion451" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1918720)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/scorpion451" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1918720); return false;" >Scorpion451</a></span> <span class="odate time_1422030079 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Jan 2015 16:21</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2214845">
									

<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">These&nbsp;are&nbsp;all&nbsp;exactly&nbsp;what&nbsp;Murphy&nbsp;was&nbsp;talking&nbsp;about</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Whats&nbsp;the&nbsp;worst&nbsp;that&nbsp;could&nbsp;happen?&nbsp;Now&nbsp;stop&nbsp;that&nbsp;from&nbsp;happening.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>#3/4:<br />
Murphy's law scenario: Assume all four bulbs will <em>always</em> burn out <em>simultaneously</em> and <em>sooner</em> than expected, and will <em>always</em> do so while there are people in the area.</p>
<p>I agree that it's got to be more than just the bulbs going out there(a power surge, anomalous influence, high powered fixtures that had been run at full capacity for 30 months straight with zero maintenance&#8230;) but the bulbs burning out was not the problem. Failure to assume that this would be the case is the problem.</p>
<p>Solution: According to Murphy, they wasted thirty seconds of warning when the first light burned out. They died because there was no regularly tested and maintained backup set of lights on a separate circuit ready to be activated at the inevitable moment when all of the regularly tested and maintained lights on the main circuit fail simultaneously for no good reason.</p>
<p>#5<br />
Murphy Scenario- The operator will be at some point be possessed by an anomalous entity, suicidal, or simply confused, and attempt to enter his own coordinates as the target of the strike.</p>
<p>Solution: Install gps trackers on vehicles and personnel. Do not allow coordinates of said vehicles and personnel to be targeted by artillery strikes without off-site confirmation.</p>
<p>(Also, as the ketergram itself suggests, avoid mixing fuel tanks full of diesel and flame-based SCP's.)</p>
<p>#6-13<br />
Murphy scenario: That, but the situation does not repeat.</p>
<p>Solution: Position observation station farther from anomaly than you think necessary to begin with.</p>
<p>Situation at hand solution for &quot;time loops are hard to accurately predict&quot;:<br />
broadcast the &quot;how to prevent everyone from dying&quot; message on loop starting several hours (accounting for travel time) before and continuing after an expected iteration begins. Use a wider focus.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

